node.text:
Last week I apparently won 2 second place awards at the Aviation Content Creator Awards (ACCA). ✈️😃 One for the highest percentage views over 200.000 and one for most average views per video upload! 🎥 @flywiththeguys accepted those awards for me and he’s bringing them everywhere! Thanks 🙌 everyone for watching my videos, I hope they help you achieve whatever it is that you want to achieve (become a 👩‍✈️👨‍✈️ pilot or something completely else you love❤️). Motivation and determination is key when it comes to achieving anything in life. I hope we can soon attend these aviation events like we used to, having a chance to meet some of you would be great!😍

Thanks everyone for watching my YouTube videos, your names should be on these Awards! ❤️ Have a great day guys, I’ll be going to bed soon as I another 🛫Islas Baleares 🛬 tomorrow! 🏝 📸 by @laluz_camera_action

✈️Life of an airline pilot: When I was based in Barcelona, 5 years ago, I flew to 🏝Ibiza every single day. In my previous company I'd also fly to Ibiza many times and in my current company I've flown there only twice. The sad part? Even after more than 500 landings at Ibiza, I've never left the airport once.... 😭crazy indeed haha! 😉 The opposite counts for the island 🏝Mallorca. The main base of my previous company was Palma de Mallorca and we had many layovers there. This week I’ll be flying to Mallorca again, but only to depart about an hour later with 200 fresh passengers on board. Life of an airline pilot doesn’t automatically mean you ‘travel the world’ or see some of the destinations 🏔🏜 you fly to. It completely depends on the kind of airline you work for and how much time you have on layovers. In my YouTube video ‘What NO ONE tells you about life as an airline pilot’ I describe all the ups and downs and different airlines I’ve worked for. ✈️ What is something you think is the best part about being a 👩‍✈️👨‍✈️ pilot? And the worst? I’d love to read your thoughts!😌😃 Have a great day guys!❤️

✈️My top 6 travel recommendations! 😌
1. Before your 🛩 flight, make sure you take some clothes in your carry on as a back-up. It can happen that suitcases don't arrive at their destination and even though they're usually delivered the day after, it is still nice to be able to go to the beach that day without wearing winter clothes. Trust me, I’ve been in those situations as a passenger and pilot 😜
2. Rent a scooter or car, online! 💪 I believe the most beautiful places can be found outside of the busy touristy places. Take Zakynthos for example, the water, caves 🌊 and views on the West/North side of the island are incredible and indescribable. However, all hotels are located on the East/South side which means that without a car, you won't even come close to seeing a little bit of the island.
3. Take an external hard disk with you and empty your camera on a regular basis. You won't be the first person who's camera gets damaged, stolen or magically goes missing.
4. 🍒🥐Eat at recommended places on @tripadvisor and book in advance. Most of those places are recommended for a reason and usually not more expensive than any other restaurant near by.
5. Ask or pay for a late check-out, especially when your return flight is in the evening.😇
6. Enjoy your holiday! 😘 Do you guys have other tips that can help people improve their holiday experience? ☺️ I'm curious to read your suggestions! Have a great week guys! ❤️

node.text: ✈️Did you know pilots greet each other in the air during the night? At night, when two aircraft flying in opposite directions approach each other, it’s quite common for the pilots to turn the landings lights 💡temporarily ON and OFF. This is done to greet each other and sometimes to increase situational awareness. Whenever the 👩‍✈️🧑‍✈️pilots of one aircraft see another aircraft approaching, they flash their landing lights and wait for the other guys to respond. Sometimes you get an answer and sometimes you don’t. I always try to respond or flash the landing lights when I see another 🛸aircraft 🚀approaching, it’s fun right? 😅 As a passenger you can see the landing lights when you are 💺seated close to the wing root and with your window blind raised. Next time you see some bright lights outside you know another aircraft is passing below or above your airplane moments later🛩 More of these facts in my ‘7 Airline Pilot Secrets You Don’t Know About’ video from 1 year ago on my YouTube Channel! 😎 Only a very few people know all 7 😉 Btw, can you guess the city in photo 4? Avgeeks only 😌✈️ Enjoy your flights! ❤️

Ask me anything I said in one of my last stories… So, here we go! Part 1 ☺️

1️⃣ How did you pay for the flight training? 
I had to take on a pilot loan, only I signed for it and no collateral was needed (watch my latest video on YouTube for the entire story).

2️⃣ Which aviation headset would you recommend, I see you wearing the Bose A20 and Bose ProFlight Series 2?
I use the Bose Proflight Series 2 on long flights and the Bose A20 on shorter flights. Both are solid investments and you can’t go wrong with either of them! More info in my review videos ☺️

3️⃣ What do you normally do on weekends? My weekends are usually at least 3 days in a row and not on Saturday and Sundays. Last year I invested a lot of time working on new projects, reading, creating and basically many things that aren’t revealed yet! 😉

4️⃣ What is the first step to become an airline pilot? The first step is to figure out why you want to become an airline pilot and if your motivation and perseverance will be enough to get you through the training. Loads of people want to become a pilot but many aren’t willing to put in the work, take the risks and overcome the obstacles which come with this profession. If you really want to become an airline pilot, I’ve covered it all in my ebook ‘Become an Airline Pilot’. See the link in my bio for more information.

5️⃣ What is your salary? 
Watch my video in which I talk about pilot salaries. It’s one of the few videos out there which tells you the entire story instead of a one sided story you read in the media. Too much information to cover here.

6️⃣ What is your skin care routine? 
I don’t drink, don’t smoke and use face oil (from holland and barrett) as my day cream. 

7️⃣ How old are you? 
29 (I know, don’t even mention it 😱😜)

I’ll cover more questions in my stories soon! Have a great week amazing people!❤️

node.text: A sensitive topic. Sometimes people ask me who makes these pictures in the cockpit. ✈️ Well, a couple of years ago we had a photographer on board, hired by the airline. He made promotional material before, during and after a ferry flight. I still have a lot of photos from back then.😌 We also had proceeding crew on the jump seat now and then who could make photos 📸whenever they wanted. Videos, like my last video on YouTube, has been made with a GoPro. 🎥 Before the flight or the turnaround we’d stick it to the window and basically ‘forget’ about it during the entire flight. 🛫🛬 After a flying day, we would grab it and see whether it recorded something useful, or nothing at all. Whether that’s allowed completely depends on the airline though. Some don’t mind as long as you use common sense, while within other airlines it’s strictly forbidden. 🤷‍♂️ This photo was made back then, by @davidemorellophotography

❤️Love yourself for who you are and who you are becoming. There are no failures in this journey called life, only lessons to be learned. The things I’ve learned about myself? Hold on! 😅

1️⃣I care a lot about deep connections with people who want the best for each other, bring each other up rather than superficial connections talking about other people or the weather. 

2️⃣My intuition never lies. Everytime I do not listen to that inner voice, I end up in trouble 😜

3️⃣Life isn’t only about flying ✈️planes✈️, even though I always thought it was. It’s about being present, experiences, meaningful connections, growth, being of service and so much more. 

4️⃣For the people I care about, I’ll go really far. 🪐 Further than I’d go for myself. 

5️⃣I don’t know why, but I can see right through people and look straight into their soul. ♏️ You can lower that shield, I already 👀 you. 

6️⃣In the past I’ve spent too much time with negative people holding on to a victim mentality. Always being there day and night, wanting to help or change them. I learned that It really doesn’t matter how much potential they have, if they don’t want to see it or take action, nothing is going to happen. 🤷‍♀️

7️⃣I want the best for other people and always see good in people..... Until they screw it up, then I’m done😂 

8️⃣I get exhausted when I have to hang around energy drainers for a long time. I just can’t put up a fake smile or behave as desired. I mentally leave the conversation. 😑

9️⃣I always tend to put myself second, instead of first. I’ll be busy fixing that these years 😌

What is something you’ve learned about yourself recently or in the last couple of years? Have a great week guys! ❤️Weekend is almost there!😘
